quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  104,7,"Which mounts directed at the hearts.{1}",1:[Covering them and penetrating them.]
  104,8,"Indeed, it [i.e., Hellfire] will be closed down upon them"
  104,9,"In extended columns.{1}",1:[Interpreted to be either columns of fire or columns of iron to which are chained the inmates of Hell.]
  105,4,"Striking them with stones of hard clay,"
  105,5,"And He made them like eaten straw.{1}",1:[i.e., husks which have been chewed by cattle. This event took place in the year of the Prophet's birth.]
  106,1,"For the accustomed security of the Quraysh{1} -",1:[i.e., the honor and reputation Allāh had given them as guardians of the Holy Kaʿbah, which allowed them to travel without fear of being harmed.]
  106,2,"Their accustomed security [in] the caravan of winter and summer{1} -",1:[i.e., the trading caravans that traveled south in winter and north in summer.]
  106,3,"Let them worship the Lord of this House,{1}",1:[i.e., the Kaʿbah.]
